WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.359
Book of 2 Corinthians here on Sunday mornings.

00:00:02.359 --> 00:00:04.800
And this morning we'll deal with the end

00:00:04.800 --> 00:00:07.079
of chapter number six and go into the first verse

00:00:07.079 --> 00:00:09.920
of chapter seven, 2 Corinthians chapter six

00:00:09.920 --> 00:00:12.399
beginning in verse number 11 is where we'll be.

00:00:12.399 --> 00:00:15.039
And we've had the opportunity, our theme for this year,

00:00:15.039 --> 00:00:16.680
God's grace is sufficient.

00:00:16.680 --> 00:00:20.559
And I'm so thankful for that wonderful biblical principle

00:00:20.559 --> 00:00:23.719
and we go through a number of things in our lives,

00:00:23.719 --> 00:00:26.360
trials and difficulties and so on and so forth.

00:00:26.360 --> 00:00:31.360
But to know that God said his grace is sufficient.

00:00:31.440 --> 00:00:34.000
And I've experienced it and I know that you have as well.

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:35.560
And so we're extremely thankful

00:00:35.560 --> 00:00:36.819
as we've studied through this book,

00:00:36.819 --> 00:00:38.720
we understand that the apostle Paul

00:00:38.720 --> 00:00:41.639
is writing back to a church that he had the opportunity

00:00:41.639 --> 00:00:45.319
to be able to minister to and to have great influence in.

00:00:45.319 --> 00:00:47.880
This church, as you read the book of 1 Corinthians

00:00:47.880 --> 00:00:49.500
had many problems and troubles

00:00:49.500 --> 00:00:52.439
and the apostle Paul is addressing a number of those things.

00:00:52.439 --> 00:00:53.560
There were some things in fact

00:00:53.560 --> 00:00:55.599
that the church had written to him about.

00:00:55.599 --> 00:00:57.360
You see that beginning in chapter seven

00:00:57.360 --> 00:01:00.240
of the first book of Corinthians.

00:01:00.240 --> 00:01:01.599
And you find that he says the things

00:01:01.599 --> 00:01:02.520
that you've written unto me.

00:01:02.520 --> 00:01:04.080
He's gonna answer those questions

00:01:04.080 --> 00:01:07.400
and I'm thankful that the Bible has the answer.

00:01:07.400 --> 00:01:08.959
And I was talking to one of my nephews

00:01:08.959 --> 00:01:12.360
just on Friday evening, he's studying biblical counseling.

00:01:12.360 --> 00:01:13.839
And I said one of the wonderful things

00:01:13.839 --> 00:01:17.440
about biblical counseling is that it's biblical counseling

00:01:17.440 --> 00:01:19.720
and you're taking people and you're leading them

00:01:19.720 --> 00:01:22.319
to the truth of God's word

00:01:22.319 --> 00:01:26.599
and God's word will help God's people.

00:01:26.599 --> 00:01:28.680
And I'm so thankful for that.

00:01:28.680 --> 00:01:30.199
This morning as we look at the text,

00:01:30.199 --> 00:01:33.360
we're reminded that the believers here in Corinth

00:01:33.360 --> 00:01:34.839
in the preceding text of scripture,

00:01:34.839 --> 00:01:38.160
it's been a couple of weeks since we've been here.

00:01:38.160 --> 00:01:40.279
I was traveling, I was preaching in Belgium last Sunday.

00:01:40.279 --> 00:01:41.959
The Sunday before was Father's Day.

00:01:41.959 --> 00:01:43.879
And so it's been about three weeks since we've been here,

00:01:43.879 --> 00:01:45.680
actually longer than that because the Sunday before that

00:01:45.680 --> 00:01:47.440
was a missions conference.

00:01:47.440 --> 00:01:49.279
But in any case, it's been a little while.

00:01:49.279 --> 00:01:52.040
So let me just remind you that the apostle Paul

00:01:52.760 --> 00:01:55.199
had the opportunity to address these believers in Corinth

00:01:55.199 --> 00:01:58.440
and to remind them of their responsibility.

00:01:58.440 --> 00:02:01.480
Often I will refer to responsibility

00:02:01.480 --> 00:02:05.440
kind of synonymously with the idea that it's a privilege.

00:02:05.440 --> 00:02:08.240
And yes, it is our responsibility

00:02:08.240 --> 00:02:10.279
to preach the gospel to every creature,

00:02:10.279 --> 00:02:13.360
but we must acknowledge that it's a privilege

00:02:13.360 --> 00:02:15.479
that has been entrusted to us.

00:02:15.479 --> 00:02:18.160
I love to tell the story.

00:02:18.160 --> 00:02:20.000
We sang the song this morning

00:02:20.039 --> 00:02:22.360
and what a wonderful hymn it is.

00:02:22.360 --> 00:02:23.839
And to remind them of the fact

00:02:23.839 --> 00:02:26.160
that we have been entrusted with the gospel.

00:02:26.160 --> 00:02:29.119
We have been privileged, allowed of God,

00:02:29.119 --> 00:02:32.720
as Paul says in 1 Thessalonians, to preach the gospel.

00:02:32.720 --> 00:02:34.000
And so he spent some time

00:02:34.000 --> 00:02:36.880
reminding these believers in Corinth.

00:02:36.880 --> 00:02:38.960
We find that they were challenged

00:02:38.960 --> 00:02:42.960
to engage in the ministry of reconciliation.

00:02:42.960 --> 00:02:45.360
He talks to them as being saved people

00:02:45.360 --> 00:02:48.199
and understanding that they had been reconciled

00:02:48.279 --> 00:02:51.759
and then tells them that God has entrusted us

00:02:51.759 --> 00:02:54.399
with this ministry of reconciliation

00:02:54.399 --> 00:02:56.839
and we are to be ambassadors.

00:02:56.839 --> 00:02:59.000
And what a blessing to be the representative

00:02:59.000 --> 00:03:02.320
of the Lord Jesus Christ and to go and tell others.

00:03:02.320 --> 00:03:05.039
We begin the sixth chapter and we find

00:03:05.960 --> 00:03:09.960
that God says that we are workers together with him.

00:03:09.960 --> 00:03:11.800
Of course, we understand that the verbiage

00:03:11.800 --> 00:03:13.960
in the book of 1 Corinthians is used

00:03:13.960 --> 00:03:16.320
that we are co-laborers, we're workers together,

00:03:16.320 --> 00:03:17.919
co-laborers with Christ.

00:03:18.440 --> 00:03:20.119
And what a blessing to think about the fact

00:03:20.119 --> 00:03:22.880
that we are workers together with God.

00:03:22.880 --> 00:03:25.199
And the apostle Paul is seeking to encourage

00:03:25.199 --> 00:03:28.119
the believers in Corinth, he's trying to help them

00:03:28.119 --> 00:03:31.160
understand what their duty and responsibility

00:03:31.160 --> 00:03:34.399
and privilege is and how they're to be engaged

00:03:34.399 --> 00:03:36.440
in the work of the ministry.

00:03:36.440 --> 00:03:39.119
We find that as we come to the end of chapter number six

00:03:39.119 --> 00:03:42.080
in 2 Corinthians that these verses of scripture

00:03:42.080 --> 00:03:44.639
are quite familiar and I would say it this way,

00:03:44.639 --> 00:03:47.679
oftentimes they are partially quoted.

00:03:48.360 --> 00:03:50.039
We look at this portion of scripture

00:03:50.039 --> 00:03:53.919
and we find that the subject of biblical separation

00:03:53.919 --> 00:03:56.320
is addressed and it's absolutely imperative

00:03:56.320 --> 00:03:58.160
that we understand this morning

00:03:58.160 --> 00:04:00.759
the importance of separation.

00:04:00.759 --> 00:04:04.160
I've titled the message simply that, biblical separation,

00:04:04.160 --> 00:04:06.919
and we look at the Bible and we understand

00:04:06.919 --> 00:04:09.960
that there's the truth of ecclesiastical separation,

00:04:09.960 --> 00:04:13.000
but there's also the truth of personal separation.

00:04:13.000 --> 00:04:15.320
As we look through the passage of scripture this morning,

00:04:15.320 --> 00:04:17.760
we are reminded of the Old Testament principle

00:04:17.760 --> 00:04:20.359
that God gives us in the little prophet of Amos,

00:04:20.359 --> 00:04:22.239
chapter three and verse number three,

00:04:22.239 --> 00:04:27.239
can two walk together except they be agreed.

00:04:27.679 --> 00:04:30.000
And we find as we begin to look at this passage

00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:32.320
of scripture, the apostle Paul is going to give

00:04:32.320 --> 00:04:35.640
some very important truth to these believers

00:04:35.640 --> 00:04:38.619
and God has chosen to preserve it for us today

00:04:38.619 --> 00:04:41.000
so that it would be to our benefit as well.

00:04:41.000 --> 00:04:42.600
Begin reading with me in verse number 11,

00:04:42.600 --> 00:04:45.279
the Bible says, O ye Corinthians,

00:04:45.279 --> 00:04:50.279
our mouth is open unto you, our heart is enlarged.

00:04:50.940 --> 00:04:52.399
You're not straightened in us,

00:04:52.399 --> 00:04:55.079
but ye are straightened in your own bowels.

00:04:55.079 --> 00:04:57.440
Now for a recompense in the same,

00:04:57.440 --> 00:05:00.880
I speak unto you as unto you my children,

00:05:00.880 --> 00:05:03.679
be ye also enlarged.

00:05:03.679 --> 00:05:06.320
We'll go through chapter seven in verse one,

00:05:06.320 --> 00:05:08.239
but let's dig right in this morning

00:05:08.239 --> 00:05:10.720
and I want you to notice just two points this morning.

00:05:10.720 --> 00:05:12.239
The first thought is this,

00:05:12.880 --> 00:05:14.799
I want you to notice with me in verses 11 through 13,

00:05:14.799 --> 00:05:17.799
Paul's care for the Corinthians.

00:05:17.799 --> 00:05:19.559
Paul's care for the Corinthians.

00:05:19.559 --> 00:05:21.679
We find that in these three verses of scripture

00:05:21.679 --> 00:05:23.320
that I've just read this morning,

00:05:23.320 --> 00:05:27.519
that Paul is seeking to express his care and concern

00:05:27.519 --> 00:05:30.679
for these believers in the church of Corinth.

00:05:30.679 --> 00:05:32.200
We find that the apostle Paul,

00:05:32.200 --> 00:05:33.839
you remember that there were some

00:05:33.839 --> 00:05:36.320
that were within the congregation of this church

00:05:36.320 --> 00:05:39.399
that had been attacking the apostle Paul

00:05:39.399 --> 00:05:42.160
and their fellowship had been strained.

00:05:43.000 --> 00:05:44.679
Remember they were saying that Paul says one thing,

00:05:44.679 --> 00:05:46.359
but he actually means something else

00:05:46.359 --> 00:05:48.799
and they're having all of this conflict

00:05:48.799 --> 00:05:50.279
with the apostle Paul.

00:05:50.279 --> 00:05:52.959
And so Paul in these verses of scripture,

00:05:52.959 --> 00:05:56.559
he's seeking to express to these believers

00:05:56.559 --> 00:05:59.519
how much he cares and loves them.

00:05:59.519 --> 00:06:01.880
We find that the apostle Paul,

00:06:01.880 --> 00:06:04.880
he had when he understood the misunderstanding

00:06:04.880 --> 00:06:08.119
as we read in chapter two and entering into chapter three

00:06:08.119 --> 00:06:10.320
of the book of second Corinthians,

00:06:10.320 --> 00:06:11.279
that what did he do?

00:06:11.279 --> 00:06:15.320
Well, before he answered them and explained,

00:06:15.320 --> 00:06:17.200
he first examined his own heart.

00:06:17.200 --> 00:06:18.920
And as he examined his own heart

00:06:18.920 --> 00:06:21.559
and took that process of self-examination,

00:06:21.559 --> 00:06:24.279
he then explained to the believers in Corinth

00:06:24.279 --> 00:06:26.799
that were saying things that were not true.

00:06:26.799 --> 00:06:29.279
And he explained to them why seeking

00:06:29.279 --> 00:06:32.600
to have some restoration in that fellowship.

00:06:32.600 --> 00:06:35.799
Paul had labored amongst these believers.

00:06:35.799 --> 00:06:38.519
Paul had a heart for these believers.

00:06:38.559 --> 00:06:42.679
He loved them and he cared deeply for them.

00:06:42.679 --> 00:06:46.000
And so Paul is seeking to express this to them.

00:06:46.000 --> 00:06:49.559
I believe that here is Paul would express to them

00:06:49.559 --> 00:06:50.640
in these few verses,

00:06:50.640 --> 00:06:53.519
it reminds us as he gives even further truth

00:06:53.519 --> 00:06:55.480
in chapter 12, hold your place here,

00:06:55.480 --> 00:06:57.359
but look at second Corinthians chapter 12

00:06:57.359 --> 00:06:59.679
and notice how the apostle Paul writes it

00:06:59.679 --> 00:07:02.359
here in these verses of scripture.

00:07:03.839 --> 00:07:07.720
The apostle Paul, because of this group in Corinth

00:07:07.720 --> 00:07:10.519
that had opposed him and the relationship,

00:07:10.519 --> 00:07:12.040
the fellowship was strained,

00:07:12.040 --> 00:07:15.799
I believe that their attitude and their spirit

00:07:15.799 --> 00:07:18.320
laid heavy upon his heart.

00:07:18.320 --> 00:07:21.239
It was something that was greatly concerned about.

00:07:21.239 --> 00:07:23.519
And we find that in the 12th chapter,

00:07:23.519 --> 00:07:25.320
notice with me in verse number 14,

00:07:25.320 --> 00:07:27.279
the Bible says, behold,

00:07:27.279 --> 00:07:30.279
the third time I am ready to come to you

00:07:30.279 --> 00:07:33.119
and I will not be burdensome to you.

00:07:33.119 --> 00:07:34.160
Notice when he says,

00:07:34.160 --> 00:07:38.279
for I seek not yours, but you.

00:07:39.320 --> 00:07:41.920
For the children ought not to lay up for the parents,

00:07:41.920 --> 00:07:44.720
but the parents for the children.

00:07:44.720 --> 00:07:49.040
And I will very gladly spend and be spent.

00:07:49.040 --> 00:07:51.880
Notice where he says for you,

00:07:51.880 --> 00:07:55.399
though the more abundantly I love you,

00:07:55.399 --> 00:07:58.799
the less I be loved.

00:07:58.799 --> 00:08:01.000
The apostle Paul cared about these believers.

00:08:01.000 --> 00:08:02.920
Why did he care so much about them?

00:08:02.920 --> 00:08:05.559
Well, he knew that God had entrusted him

00:08:05.559 --> 00:08:09.559
with a responsibility to minister to them spiritually,

00:08:09.559 --> 00:08:11.959
to be a spiritual leader in their lives.

00:08:11.959 --> 00:08:15.679
And he knew that they one day would stand

00:08:15.679 --> 00:08:17.519
before the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:08:17.519 --> 00:08:20.600
And he desired that on that day,

00:08:20.600 --> 00:08:24.399
they would be able to stand before Christ complete.

00:08:24.399 --> 00:08:28.559
That he had that desire, that longing for these,

00:08:28.559 --> 00:08:31.920
that God had given him the privilege of ministering to.

00:08:31.920 --> 00:08:34.559
And what was happening is because of this conflict,

00:08:34.559 --> 00:08:36.559
because of their own attitude,

00:08:36.559 --> 00:08:40.919
we find that they were resisting the message

00:08:40.919 --> 00:08:45.119
that God had given Paul to deliver to them.

00:08:45.119 --> 00:08:47.359
Paul understood that it was God's word.

00:08:47.359 --> 00:08:50.840
Paul understood that it was profitable for those believers.

00:08:50.840 --> 00:08:54.200
Paul understood that what God had given him,

00:08:54.200 --> 00:08:58.640
these people needed, but they weren't gonna receive it

00:08:58.640 --> 00:09:01.780
because they had angst against Paul.

00:09:02.640 --> 00:09:03.479
So what's Paul doing?

00:09:03.479 --> 00:09:05.299
Well, before he's gonna give them the great truth

00:09:05.299 --> 00:09:07.500
that we're gonna look at here in just a few moments,

00:09:07.500 --> 00:09:11.700
he first lets them know how much he cares about them,

00:09:11.700 --> 00:09:13.460
how much he loves them.

00:09:13.460 --> 00:09:16.020
We find that in Galatians chapter four,

00:09:16.020 --> 00:09:18.739
not concerning this particular church, obviously,

00:09:18.739 --> 00:09:21.619
but the Bible tells us in Galatians four,

00:09:21.619 --> 00:09:24.700
as Paul is writing back to those churches

00:09:24.700 --> 00:09:26.580
in the region of Galatia, he says,

00:09:26.580 --> 00:09:28.900
"'Am I therefore become your enemy

00:09:28.900 --> 00:09:32.020
"'because I tell you the truth?'

00:09:32.020 --> 00:09:34.020
Paul understood the importance of truth.

00:09:34.020 --> 00:09:34.940
He had been entrusted.

00:09:34.940 --> 00:09:37.219
He understood that God's word is truth,

00:09:37.219 --> 00:09:40.179
and he faithfully preached the word of God,

00:09:40.179 --> 00:09:43.239
but yet he says, "'Have I become your enemy

00:09:43.239 --> 00:09:45.380
"'because I tell you the truth?'

00:09:45.380 --> 00:09:47.940
You know what's sad is that there are many people today

00:09:47.940 --> 00:09:49.580
that do not know the truth.

00:09:50.580 --> 00:09:52.739
You know what's even more burdensome

00:09:52.739 --> 00:09:53.700
is there's a number of people

00:09:53.700 --> 00:09:56.419
that don't want to know the truth.

00:09:57.260 --> 00:09:58.099
They're just willingly ignorant,

00:09:58.099 --> 00:09:59.979
as it says in 2 Peter chapter three.

00:09:59.979 --> 00:10:02.019
They just don't wanna know the truth.

00:10:02.019 --> 00:10:05.339
They wanna continue down the path that they're traveling,

00:10:05.339 --> 00:10:07.659
believing whatever it is that they're believing.

00:10:07.659 --> 00:10:10.739
We have in our society today groups of people

00:10:10.739 --> 00:10:13.439
that will say, well, this is my truth and your truth

00:10:13.439 --> 00:10:14.419
and so on and so forth.

00:10:14.419 --> 00:10:17.359
The reality is that truth is not subjective.

00:10:17.359 --> 00:10:21.079
Truth is founded upon the Lord Jesus Christ and his word.

00:10:21.079 --> 00:10:23.099
And Paul says, if I'm giving you the truth,

00:10:23.099 --> 00:10:25.859
why are you treating me like I'm an enemy?

00:10:25.859 --> 00:10:26.899
What was Paul trying to do?

00:10:26.899 --> 00:10:29.459
He's trying to give them the truth to help them.

00:10:29.459 --> 00:10:30.859
You ever have somebody get upset with you

00:10:30.859 --> 00:10:32.459
because you give them the truth?

00:10:33.539 --> 00:10:36.599
The gospel's offensive, amen?

00:10:36.599 --> 00:10:38.599
And Lauren, I don't know where Lauren is,

00:10:38.599 --> 00:10:39.439
oh, there she is.

00:10:39.439 --> 00:10:40.859
You asked me a question a few weeks ago

00:10:40.859 --> 00:10:42.599
about people being upset about door knocking,

00:10:42.599 --> 00:10:44.779
and since then, I've gotten some calls.

00:10:44.779 --> 00:10:45.899
I'm not saying it's your fault,

00:10:45.899 --> 00:10:48.219
but man, we got a phone call where in Belgium,

00:10:48.219 --> 00:10:51.979
somebody just absolutely ripped us.

00:10:51.979 --> 00:10:53.699
I mean, just the profanity

00:10:53.699 --> 00:10:55.779
and just a short little voice message

00:10:55.779 --> 00:10:57.779
that was left on the voicemail at church

00:10:57.779 --> 00:11:00.779
about the fact that we left some gospel literature

00:11:00.779 --> 00:11:02.219
on their door.

00:11:02.219 --> 00:11:03.519
They don't want the truth.

00:11:04.699 --> 00:11:08.139
You know, I wasn't mad about the voicemail.

00:11:08.139 --> 00:11:09.459
My heart was saddened.

00:11:10.659 --> 00:11:12.979
Because that individual identified themselves

00:11:12.979 --> 00:11:17.979
on that phone call as being a proud pagan atheist.

00:11:20.579 --> 00:11:22.139
That's how they described themselves.

00:11:22.139 --> 00:11:24.539
And here's the immediate thought that I had.

00:11:24.539 --> 00:11:28.859
They held in their hand the very truth

00:11:31.439 --> 00:11:33.419
that would save their soul.

00:11:34.979 --> 00:11:36.019
And they rejected it.

00:11:37.219 --> 00:11:40.939
And they got mad about the truth.

00:11:40.939 --> 00:11:41.779
It's nothing new.

00:11:41.779 --> 00:11:44.259
Paul experienced this, but Paul's trying to convey

00:11:44.259 --> 00:11:46.859
and to communicate to the believers in Corinth,

00:11:46.859 --> 00:11:50.339
I love you, I'm trying to help you.

00:11:50.339 --> 00:11:52.879
You ever see children that don't like the instruction

00:11:52.879 --> 00:11:54.119
