notice what Paul says, but we were gentle among you.

00:12:44.239 --> 00:12:47.599
Even as a nurse cherisheth her children,

00:12:47.599 --> 00:12:51.279
so being affectionately desirous of you,

00:12:51.279 --> 00:12:53.479
we were willing to have imparted unto you

00:12:53.479 --> 00:12:57.199
not the gospel of God only, but also our own souls,

00:12:57.199 --> 00:13:01.559
because ye were dear unto us.

00:13:01.559 --> 00:13:03.399
The reality this morning is that Paul,

00:13:03.399 --> 00:13:05.679
notice what he says in verse number 11 back in our text.

00:13:05.679 --> 00:13:09.119
He says, oh, ye Corinthians, notice he says,

00:13:09.119 --> 00:13:12.459
our mouth is open unto you.

00:13:12.459 --> 00:13:15.279
Paul believed because he understood the work

00:13:15.279 --> 00:13:16.739
that God had entrusted him with.

00:13:16.739 --> 00:13:20.439
Listen, Paul knew his position as being an Apostle.

00:13:20.439 --> 00:13:22.159
Paul knew his calling.

00:13:22.159 --> 00:13:25.919
He knew that God had called him to be a preacher

00:13:25.919 --> 00:13:28.359
of the gospel of the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:13:28.359 --> 00:13:31.959
God had made it clear, and Paul clearly communicates

00:13:31.959 --> 00:13:34.359
throughout the epistles that he knew

00:13:34.359 --> 00:13:36.999
that he was doing the work of God.

00:13:38.719 --> 00:13:40.359
He says, I'm warning you, why?

00:13:40.359 --> 00:13:44.279
To present you perfect or complete at that day.

00:13:44.279 --> 00:13:47.119
He says that to the people in Colossae

00:13:47.119 --> 00:13:50.239
in Colossians chapter one, and we find that Paul knew,

00:13:51.079 --> 00:13:52.359
and he says, our mouth is open unto you.

00:13:52.359 --> 00:13:57.359
He continues in verse 11 and says, our heart is enlarged.

00:13:57.779 --> 00:14:00.439
Paul says, listen, I'm not mad at you.

00:14:00.439 --> 00:14:03.319
I'm not, there's no, it's not on my side.

00:14:03.319 --> 00:14:06.079
You're resisting me, and I want you to know

00:14:06.079 --> 00:14:07.959
that my mouth is open to you,

00:14:07.959 --> 00:14:11.039
that my heart is enlarged unto you,

00:14:11.039 --> 00:14:13.799
and we find that then in verses 12 and 13,

00:14:13.799 --> 00:14:15.879
what Paul was communicating, he says,

00:14:15.879 --> 00:14:17.539
ye are not straightened in us.

00:14:17.539 --> 00:14:20.139
Again, it's not the fact that I have something

00:14:20.959 --> 00:14:24.019
against you, but ye are straightened in your own bowels,

00:14:24.019 --> 00:14:25.979
not for a recompense in the same.

00:14:25.979 --> 00:14:28.819
I speak as unto my children.

00:14:28.819 --> 00:14:31.019
Be ye also enlarged.

00:14:31.019 --> 00:14:32.059
What is he doing?

00:14:32.059 --> 00:14:34.579
Paul is communicating to them, and he's desiring

00:14:34.579 --> 00:14:36.339
that their fellowship be restored.

00:14:36.339 --> 00:14:38.619
He's literally pleading with them.

00:14:38.619 --> 00:14:41.659
He loves them, and he desires to minister to them,

00:14:41.659 --> 00:14:45.659
and he wants them to open their hearts to him

00:14:46.659 --> 00:14:50.579
because he knew that if their heart was closed to him,

00:14:50.579 --> 00:14:54.419
they weren't gonna receive what God had for them.

00:14:55.739 --> 00:14:58.259
I've had times over the years where I'd get a phone call

00:14:58.259 --> 00:15:01.579
from someone and say, hey, my neighbor or my relative,

00:15:01.579 --> 00:15:03.779
they need some help, would you go help them?

00:15:04.699 --> 00:15:06.859
And I say, nope, you can give them my phone number,

00:15:06.859 --> 00:15:09.459
and if they want help, they can call me.

00:15:09.459 --> 00:15:10.299
You know why I do that?

00:15:10.299 --> 00:15:12.499
Because I've learned that if I try to go help someone

00:15:12.499 --> 00:15:13.619
that doesn't really want help,

00:15:13.619 --> 00:15:16.499
it's just absolutely torturous for me.

00:15:19.139 --> 00:15:21.539
And the reality is that Paul's saying,

00:15:21.539 --> 00:15:24.259
I have something that's beneficial for you.

00:15:24.259 --> 00:15:25.379
Why, because he's Paul?

00:15:25.379 --> 00:15:27.739
No, because it's God's word.

00:15:27.739 --> 00:15:29.459
He knows, he says all scripture is given

00:15:29.459 --> 00:15:33.699
by inspiration of God and is profitable.

00:15:33.699 --> 00:15:35.819
And so Paul says, I have this for you,

00:15:35.819 --> 00:15:38.139
and I want you to know how much I care for you

00:15:38.139 --> 00:15:40.139
and how much I love you.

00:15:40.139 --> 00:15:41.999
And a man asked me a number of years ago

00:15:41.999 --> 00:15:44.159
as I would share the gospel with him repeatedly

00:15:44.159 --> 00:15:46.159
and he would just continue to resist

00:15:46.159 --> 00:15:47.839
and to resist and to reject.

00:15:47.839 --> 00:15:51.239
And I find that eventually on one particular day,

00:15:51.239 --> 00:15:55.559
he looked straight in my face and he said, why do you care?

00:15:56.839 --> 00:15:58.039
It's what he said to me.

00:15:59.319 --> 00:16:01.799
He said this, he followed up the statement by saying,

00:16:01.799 --> 00:16:05.399
why do you care by saying, so what if I go to hell?

00:16:06.239 --> 00:16:07.479
It's what he said to me.

00:16:07.479 --> 00:16:09.879
I couldn't imagine the words that I was hearing.

00:16:10.799 --> 00:16:14.519
And he said, but why do you care if I don't even care?

00:16:14.519 --> 00:16:15.399
It's what he said.

00:16:16.559 --> 00:16:18.359
You know what I told him?

00:16:18.359 --> 00:16:19.839
I said, I understand the truth of God's word

00:16:19.839 --> 00:16:21.359
and I believe it.

00:16:21.359 --> 00:16:23.239
You're gonna die one day.

00:16:23.239 --> 00:16:25.399
You're gonna go to heaven or hell.

00:16:25.399 --> 00:16:28.519
God loves you and he wants you to be saved.

00:16:28.519 --> 00:16:29.639
He died for you.

00:16:30.879 --> 00:16:32.239
And here's what I told this individual.

00:16:32.239 --> 00:16:34.439
I said, listen, I'm going to heaven

00:16:34.439 --> 00:16:35.959
whether you get saved or not.

00:16:36.919 --> 00:16:39.159
It's not necessarily a benefit.

00:16:39.159 --> 00:16:40.879
It's not like it helps me get to heaven

00:16:40.879 --> 00:16:44.439
because no, I want you to go to heaven with me.

00:16:45.639 --> 00:16:47.679
But I'm going to heaven whether you receive

00:16:47.679 --> 00:16:49.919
or reject the truth of the gospel.

00:16:49.919 --> 00:16:52.159
And the reality is that Paul, listen,

00:16:52.159 --> 00:16:54.439
he understood his walk with God.

00:16:54.439 --> 00:16:57.079
Paul understood, he talks about at the end

00:16:57.079 --> 00:16:59.279
of the book of Second Timothy that he's finished,

00:16:59.279 --> 00:17:01.359
he's completed, he's done the work

00:17:01.359 --> 00:17:02.519
that God's called him to do.

00:17:02.519 --> 00:17:04.679
He knew that there would be a crown for him.

00:17:04.679 --> 00:17:07.279
He knew that he had, not that he's perfect,

00:17:07.279 --> 00:17:10.959
but he was seeking to do what God had called him to do.

00:17:10.959 --> 00:17:13.319
He said that he exercised himself

00:17:13.319 --> 00:17:16.119
to have always a conscience void of offense

00:17:16.119 --> 00:17:17.919
before God and man.

00:17:17.919 --> 00:17:20.759
And so Paul was seeking to walk with God,

00:17:20.759 --> 00:17:24.199
but he wanted others to benefit from the truth

00:17:24.199 --> 00:17:26.159
that God had given him.

00:17:26.159 --> 00:17:27.239
So what does he do?

00:17:27.239 --> 00:17:31.079
He expresses his care, his love, his concern.

00:17:32.239 --> 00:17:33.839
It's not a Bible verse.

00:17:33.879 --> 00:17:36.999
It's not a Bible verse, but I believe it is a principle

00:17:36.999 --> 00:17:40.759
that is certainly founded upon biblical truth,

00:17:40.759 --> 00:17:41.599
and that is this.

00:17:41.599 --> 00:17:44.519
Many times people don't care how much you know

00:17:44.519 --> 00:17:47.039
until they know how much you care.

00:17:47.039 --> 00:17:49.279
And we've used that phrase at times,

00:17:49.279 --> 00:17:52.679
and we understand that, again, it's not a Bible verse,

00:17:52.679 --> 00:17:55.039
but I believe the concept and the thought

00:17:55.039 --> 00:17:58.479
is certainly founded upon biblical principle.

00:17:59.359 --> 00:18:03.879
This morning before Paul gets into the subject of separation

00:18:03.879 --> 00:18:06.759
we find that he expresses his care

00:18:06.759 --> 00:18:09.399
to these believers in Corinth.

00:18:09.399 --> 00:18:10.999
I wonder this morning,

00:18:10.999 --> 00:18:13.879
how many people truly know that we care about them,

00:18:13.879 --> 00:18:15.479
that we love them?

00:18:15.479 --> 00:18:17.719
You know, people have all kinds of ideas

00:18:17.719 --> 00:18:21.199
about church and religion, quote unquote.

00:18:21.199 --> 00:18:24.679
They think that somehow you're going to benefit

00:18:24.679 --> 00:18:25.759
or I'm going to benefit,

00:18:25.759 --> 00:18:28.119
that we're trying to get some gain for ourselves,

00:18:28.759 --> 00:18:30.959
but the reality is that we're simply seeking

00:18:30.959 --> 00:18:34.959
to impart truth to someone that will benefit them.

00:18:36.119 --> 00:18:38.159
Now, do we seek to teach them all things

00:18:38.159 --> 00:18:39.440
whatsoever I've commanded you?

00:18:39.440 --> 00:18:42.159
Yes, we do seek to disciple and to train

00:18:42.159 --> 00:18:44.479
and to teach the truth of God's word.

00:18:44.479 --> 00:18:45.320
Why?

00:18:45.320 --> 00:18:47.359
Because it's God's plan that all of God's people

00:18:47.359 --> 00:18:48.719
are conformed to the image of Christ,

00:18:48.719 --> 00:18:51.119
and you're going to stand before Christ one day.

00:18:51.959 --> 00:18:53.239
But Paul says, I love you.

00:18:53.239 --> 00:18:55.959
My heart's, my mouth is open unto you.

00:18:56.839 --> 00:18:59.119
Our heart is enlarged.

00:18:59.119 --> 00:19:00.079
So what does he say?

00:19:00.079 --> 00:19:02.079
Be ye also enlarged.

00:19:03.760 --> 00:19:06.119
We find that Paul's care for the Corinthians

00:19:06.119 --> 00:19:08.119
is revealed in verses 11 through 13.

00:19:08.119 --> 00:19:09.839
As we look at the remainder of the text

00:19:09.839 --> 00:19:11.559
and enter into the seventh chapter,

00:19:11.559 --> 00:19:16.159
we find number two, Paul's counsel to the Corinthians.

00:19:16.159 --> 00:19:17.679
Paul's counsel to the Corinthians.

00:19:17.679 --> 00:19:22.119
By the way, counsel is regularly received far better

00:19:22.119 --> 00:19:24.440
from someone or by someone

00:19:24.440 --> 00:19:26.279
that knows that you care about them.

00:19:27.359 --> 00:19:29.159
So you care about them.

00:19:29.159 --> 00:19:30.760
He says this in verse 14,

00:19:30.760 --> 00:19:34.799
be ye not unequally yoked together with unbelievers.

00:19:34.799 --> 00:19:37.440
For what fellowship hath righteousness with unrighteousness

00:19:37.440 --> 00:19:40.359
and what communion hath light with darkness?

00:19:40.359 --> 00:19:43.239
And what concord hath Christ with Belial

00:19:43.239 --> 00:19:47.399
or what part hath he that believeth with an infidel?

00:19:47.399 --> 00:19:51.320
And what agreement hath the temple of God with idols?

00:19:51.320 --> 00:19:54.079
For ye are the temple of the living God

00:19:54.719 --> 00:19:57.320
and as God hath said, I will dwell in them and walk in them

00:19:57.320 --> 00:20:00.320
and I will be their God and they shall be mine.

00:20:00.320 --> 00:20:03.460
My people, wherefore, come out from among them,

00:20:03.460 --> 00:20:06.220
and be ye separate, saith the Lord,

00:20:06.220 --> 00:20:08.360
and touch not the unclean thing,

00:20:08.360 --> 00:20:11.160
and I will receive you and will be a father unto you,

00:20:11.160 --> 00:20:13.140
and you shall be my sons and daughters,

00:20:13.140 --> 00:20:14.700
saith the Lord Almighty,

00:20:14.700 --> 00:20:18.600
having therefore these promises, dearly beloved.

00:20:18.600 --> 00:20:20.880
Let us cleanse ourselves from all filthiness

00:20:20.880 --> 00:20:22.400
of the flesh and spirit,

00:20:22.400 --> 00:20:26.440
perfecting holiness in the fear of God.

00:20:26.440 --> 00:20:28.840
What great counsel that we read

00:20:28.840 --> 00:20:30.600
in these verses of scripture.

00:20:30.600 --> 00:20:33.680
And we find that the counsel is really given

00:20:33.680 --> 00:20:37.240
to us in verse 14, and then again, repeated in verse 17.

00:20:37.240 --> 00:20:38.580
And here's the counsel,

00:20:38.580 --> 00:20:43.580
be ye not unequally yoked together with unbelievers.

00:20:43.760 --> 00:20:47.480
He rephrases it and says it this way in verse 17,

00:20:47.480 --> 00:20:50.220
wherefore, come out from among them,

00:20:50.220 --> 00:20:54.040
and be ye separate, saith the Lord,

00:20:54.040 --> 00:20:55.700
and touch not the unclean thing,

00:20:55.700 --> 00:20:57.760
and I will receive you.

00:20:57.760 --> 00:21:01.120
We find that the counsel is very straightforward.

00:21:01.120 --> 00:21:05.260
Be not unequally yoked together with unbelievers.

00:21:05.260 --> 00:21:07.200
It's very straightforward, it's simple.

00:21:08.400 --> 00:21:12.500
Then Paul spends the next couple of verses of scripture

00:21:12.500 --> 00:21:14.900
in providing examples

00:21:14.900 --> 00:21:17.780
as he explains this truth of separation.

00:21:17.780 --> 00:21:19.980
Notice the explanation that is given

00:21:19.980 --> 00:21:23.140
beginning in verse 14 and really down through verse 16.

00:21:23.140 --> 00:21:25.480
In verse 14, the counsel had been given,

00:21:25.500 --> 00:21:28.080
be not unequally yoked together with unbelievers,

00:21:28.080 --> 00:21:29.780
but then we find the explanation.

00:21:29.780 --> 00:21:31.080
Notice he says this,

00:21:31.080 --> 00:21:35.020
and he explains it by asking a series of questions.

00:21:35.020 --> 00:21:39.080
The questions that he asks are actually very easy to answer.

00:21:39.080 --> 00:21:42.360
Notice he says the first one in verse 14,

00:21:42.360 --> 00:21:46.900
he says, for what fellowship hath righteousness

00:21:46.900 --> 00:21:49.000
with unrighteousness?

00:21:49.000 --> 00:21:50.560
The things that are right

00:21:50.560 --> 00:21:51.760
and the things that are not right.

00:21:51.760 --> 00:21:55.100
What fellowship do they have one with the other?

00:21:55.760 --> 00:21:58.560
It's pretty obvious as Paul is seeking to explain

00:21:58.560 --> 00:22:00.260
the counsel that he's just given

00:22:00.260 --> 00:22:02.020
to these believers in Corinth,

00:22:02.020 --> 00:22:03.940
and he begins to ask them these questions.

00:22:03.940 --> 00:22:06.600
What's the purpose of asking the question?

00:22:06.600 --> 00:22:08.600
Is the purpose of asking the question

00:22:08.600 --> 00:22:12.080
for Paul to gain some knowledge or wisdom?

00:22:12.080 --> 00:22:16.080
See, sometimes we ask questions for information, right?

00:22:17.240 --> 00:22:19.240
I don't know something, so I ask someone a question

00:22:19.240 --> 00:22:23.560
so that I can gain information because I am not aware.

00:22:23.620 --> 00:22:27.220
The questions that are asked here are not for information.

00:22:27.220 --> 00:22:28.680
You ever hear somebody use the phrase

00:22:28.680 --> 00:22:32.360
that that's a thought-provoking question?

00:22:32.360 --> 00:22:36.320
Sometimes a question is asked so that the receiver,

00:22:36.320 --> 00:22:38.360
the recipient of that question,

00:22:38.360 --> 00:22:41.400
has a time of really considering

00:22:41.400 --> 00:22:44.740
and contemplating in their own hearts and minds

00:22:44.740 --> 00:22:46.840
the truth that is being given.

00:22:47.740 --> 00:22:50.740
And here is the apostle Paul ask these questions

00:22:50.740 --> 00:22:52.340
to these believers in Corinth,

00:22:52.460 --> 00:22:55.020
and he says, what fellowship hath righteousness

00:22:55.020 --> 00:22:56.100
with unrighteousness?

00:22:56.100 --> 00:22:59.020
He's not really necessarily seeking information

00:22:59.020 --> 00:23:00.820
or expecting them to answer,

00:23:00.820 --> 00:23:04.480
but he's trying to communicate to them the truth

00:23:04.480 --> 00:23:07.820
that hey, why is the counsel to be separate?

00:23:07.820 --> 00:23:12.820
Why is the counsel to be not unequally yoked together

00:23:12.860 --> 00:23:13.700
with unbelievers?

00:23:13.700 --> 00:23:15.660
Because there's no fellowship

00:23:15.660 --> 00:23:18.380
