00:23:19.380 --> 00:23:23.660
We live in a land, we live in a time,

00:23:23.660 --> 00:23:25.340
and it's nothing new for us.

00:23:25.340 --> 00:23:27.140
It's always been this way,

00:23:28.380 --> 00:23:32.180
where they call good evil and evil good.

00:23:32.180 --> 00:23:35.460
We see the prophets of old using that phraseology.

00:23:35.460 --> 00:23:39.380
We understand that as we would not only see in a society

00:23:39.380 --> 00:23:42.700
as we've seen in previous periods of history,

00:23:42.700 --> 00:23:45.140
but even in our own society today,

00:23:45.140 --> 00:23:48.100
where not only do they call evil good and good evil,

00:23:48.780 --> 00:23:51.860
but they legislate wickedness.

00:23:51.860 --> 00:23:54.060
We see it, we understand it.

00:23:54.060 --> 00:23:57.140
It's not hard for us as believers

00:23:57.140 --> 00:24:00.700
to look at the question that is asked in verse number 14

00:24:00.700 --> 00:24:05.700
of what fellowship hath righteousness with unrighteousness.

00:24:06.180 --> 00:24:08.100
The answer is there's no fellowship.

00:24:10.440 --> 00:24:12.340
We see that he asks another question

00:24:12.340 --> 00:24:13.980
at the end of verse 14.

00:24:14.020 --> 00:24:19.020
What communion hath light with darkness?

00:24:19.860 --> 00:24:23.100
You know, I'm thankful that I was in darkness,

00:24:23.100 --> 00:24:24.740
but not any longer.

00:24:24.740 --> 00:24:25.820
Amen.

00:24:25.820 --> 00:24:27.580
We are children of the light.

00:24:27.580 --> 00:24:29.700
We are to walk as children of light.

00:24:29.700 --> 00:24:31.300
You read the book of Ephesians,

00:24:31.300 --> 00:24:34.260
and you understand that we were, past tense,

00:24:34.260 --> 00:24:35.660
if you're saved this morning,

00:24:35.660 --> 00:24:38.740
if you've trusted Christ as your personal savior,

00:24:38.740 --> 00:24:43.420
what you were in blindness and in darkness without Christ

00:24:43.420 --> 00:24:46.140
and all of that, listen, that's our past,

00:24:46.140 --> 00:24:48.980
but now as children of light,

00:24:48.980 --> 00:24:52.580
we're to walk and behave a certain way.

00:24:52.580 --> 00:24:57.020
And he says, what communion hath light with darkness?

00:24:57.020 --> 00:25:01.179
You walk into a dark room and you turn on the light

00:25:01.179 --> 00:25:04.220
and the darkness dispels, right?

00:25:04.220 --> 00:25:05.540
We understand that.

00:25:05.540 --> 00:25:09.220
Men loveth darkness rather than light.

00:25:09.220 --> 00:25:12.679
We understand the darkness of the society in which we live,

00:25:12.679 --> 00:25:15.240
but listen, he's talking about the fact,

00:25:15.240 --> 00:25:19.000
this principle, this council being unequally yoked together

00:25:19.000 --> 00:25:22.679
with unbelievers, and he's explaining this.

00:25:22.679 --> 00:25:25.020
Why do we talk about biblical separation?

00:25:25.020 --> 00:25:28.360
Why is it important that we understand the principle

00:25:28.360 --> 00:25:31.000
that the apostle Paul is giving,

00:25:31.000 --> 00:25:33.980
not only to the people in Corinth, but to us,

00:25:33.980 --> 00:25:37.960
that we're to be careful and to be aware of this council

00:25:37.960 --> 00:25:39.480
and the importance of separation,

00:25:39.480 --> 00:25:42.360
because there's no fellowship between righteousness

00:25:42.360 --> 00:25:43.279
